      static <T> void doesNotHaveClass(Assert<? extends T> $receiver, kotlin.reflect.KClass<? extends T> kclass)
      Asserts the value does not have the expected kotlin class. This is an exact match, so assert("test").doesNotHaveClass(String::class) is fails but assert("test").doesNotHaveClass(Any::class) is successful.
